"download.py"
Downloads all data for PM10 and PM2.5 for all EU countries, filtered by aggregation type (daily) and saves them as parquet files in the data/daily directory.

Because some countries are missing daily aggregation for PM10 and PM2.5 there are 2 other scripts called "download_hourly_pm2-5.py" and "download_hourly_pm10.py" which download hourly data for the countries that are missing.

"aggregate.py"
Aggregates the hourly data for PM10 and PM2.5 to daily data and saves them as parquet files in the data/daily directory.

This way we now have daily data for PM10 and PM2.5 for all EU countries, which we can load into DuckDB and use for our dashboard.